	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64967389"><p>When the web was first created, the nerd world was asked how to protect kids from <i> <b>the whole internet</b> </i>.

</p><p>So we did what TV builders did, and provided parental controls.  The app store can ask the parental controls if this is a kid.

</p><p>If it has to be done with no code changes to the controls, a first app could try to open an age-restricted site, to see if the controls kick in. If so, no age-restricted apps. If not, download the asked-for app.

</p><p>Ditto for sites with both adult and kid content.</p></div>
	</div>

